@node "FREEWARE" "FREEware"

 I am releasing these objects as freeware because this is my way of giving back
to all the other Amiga user that have written some really cool programs.

 These objects are based on the plans in "STAR WARS THE ESSENTIAL GUIDE TO
VEHICLES AND VESSELS" [ISBN 0-345-39299-X] DEL REY 

 tHE ARCHIVE CAN BE FREELY DISTRIBUTED AS LONG AS ALL FILES REMAIN INTACT. IF
YOU WANT TO CONVERT THEM INTO ANOTHER FORMAT, YOU MAY REPLACE THE OBJECTS, BUT
KEEP THIS GUIDE FILE AND ADD ANY INFORMATION NEEDED TO IT.  (IF YOU NEED AN
OTHER FORMAT @{"E-MAIL ME" link "author" 0} AND I WILL RUN THEM THROUGH PIXEL PRO AND SEND THEM TO
YOU). IF YOU INCLUDE IT ON A CD (EXCEPT THE AMINET) YOU MUST SEND ME A COPY OF
THE CD.

 STAR WARS IS A (R),TM, AND COPYRIGHT LUCASFILM Ltd. All rights Reserved
@endnode

@node "AT-PT" "AT-PT TRANSPORT"

 AT-PT.ibj

 Imperial All Terrain Transport (from Dark Force rising?)

 Scale: 1m=20 imagine units (this is a guess, the plans didn't have a scale)

 There are 6 states:
   -DEFAULT          standing up
   -LEFT-FORWARD     left leg stepped forward
   -RIGHT-FORWARD    right leg stepped forward
   -RIGHT-UP         right leg lifted strait up
   -LEFT-UP          left leg lifted strait up
   -PARK             bent down for driver to enter

 to walk  DEFAULT > LEFT-UP > LEFT-FORWARD > RIGHT-UP > RIGHT-FORWARD > (REPEAT
WITH LEFT-UP)

 THE PROJECT @{b}WALKER.IMP@{ub} IS AN EXAMPLE OF A WALKING CYCLE. PUT THE PROJECT IN
YOUR @{b}WORK:@{ub} DRIVE OR ASSIGN @{b}WORK:@{ub} TO THE LOCATION OF @{b}WALKER.IMP@{ub}.


 @{u}TEXTURES@{uu}:@{fg shine}Dirt@{fg text} (standard Imagine texture),and @{fg shine}warningstripes@{fg text}(part of the texture
studio)
@endnode

